efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n * m) where m is number of distinct character runs (m ≤ n)
space complexity: O(n * m)
energy implications: MEDIUM
explanation: Uses dynamic programming with prefix sums to count valid subsequences efficiently. Groups consecutive identical characters into runs, then computes ways to choose lengths for each run while maintaining total length ≥ k. Prefix sums reduce inner loop to O(1) per state.

